  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Peel and then grate one small turmeric root, before chopping slightly and adding to the pan.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Grate a little nutmeg, and then add it to the pan together with the cinnamon and cardamom.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Keep on a low heat stirring regularly for around five minutes until slightly steaming. Do not boil as the milk will burn.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Check for taste and add more spice as required.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Once ready, use a wooden spoon to strain the turmeric from the liquid as you transfer into a cup. For extra comfort, warm the cup with hot water before pouring the liquid from the pan. Makes one serving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">A great calming drink found in nytimes. It is working. Tested. Recipe by Matilda Goad.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://zverbatim.github.com/images/posts/MelodyGardot-JAttendrai.png" /></entry><entry><title type="html">J’attendrai - Ibrahim Maalouf, Melody Gardot</title><link href="http://zverbatim.github.com/j-attendrai/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="J'attendrai - Ibrahim Maalouf, Melody Gardot" /><published>2017-01-09T00:00:00-06:00</published><updated>2017-01-09T00:00:00-06:00</updated><id>http://zverbatim.github.com/j-attendrai</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://zverbatim.github.com/j-attendrai/">&lt;iframe src=&quot;https://open.spotify.com/embed?uri=spotify:track:3Ks3YWCoSba0Le2zzQYxKM&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;380&quot; height=&quot;300&quot; allowtransparency=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
